# ── DATABASE_URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️ Local dev MUST use the Neon **dev** branch, NOT prod. Prod (`main` branch)
# and local dev previously shared one URL, so `medusa develop`/`exec` wrote to
# prod (that's how 70+ duplicate stores/keys appeared). Keep them separate:
#   • Local dev → Neon `dev` branch (ep-twilight-poetry-*). Fetch with:
#       neonctl connection-string dev --project-id shiny-paper-72860331 --pooled
#   • Prod → Neon `main` branch — lives ONLY in GCP Secret Manager / Cloud Run.
#   • One-off prod ops (backfill, cleanup): put the prod URL in `.env.prod`
#     (gitignored) and run e.g. `dotenv -e .env.prod -- npx medusa exec …`.
DATABASE_URL=
DB_NAME=medusa-backend
# Pin the storefront sales channel so product creation never guesses among stores.
MEDUSA_SALES_CHANNEL_ID=sc_01KSK1J0V81P4EPY9G0JAPX353
